article.linkText: Moffatt, Records score 15, Colgate downs Holy Cross 85-55
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Ryan Moffatt and Keegan Records both scored 15 points in Colgate's 85-55 win over Holy Cross on Wednesday night. Moffatt added eight rebounds for the Raiders (18-8, 12-1 Patriot League). Records shot 7 of 11 from the field. Jeff Woodward and Braeden Smith both contributed 12 points. The Raiders picked up their 10th straight win. The Crusaders (8-18, 5-8) were led by Joseph Octave, who recorded 13 points. DeAndre Williams added 11 points, eight rebounds and four assists for Holy Cross. In addition, Caleb Kenney had 11 points and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
